VinZ
"Swan Lake"
Edition: 35
Size: 50 x 70 cm
Two layer hand-pulled screenprint
Each print is unique and has been hand-painted with 10 extra colours by VinZ. 
Signed And Numbered.

VinZ returns for his second print with Street Art News after his first edition was an instant sell-out. The Spaniard used a multi-step process to create this unique print. Vinz first photographed nude models, then he painted animal heads onto large-scale prints of the human figures. This process creates hybrid subjects with a system of symbols attached to birds, aka freedom.

"Swan Lake" will be available on Wednesday, December 18th at 4PM UK

name: Borondo "El Peso De La Corona"
description: Borondo "El Peso De La Corona" Edition: 35 Size: 70 x 50 cm One layer hand-pulled screen-print - Hand-Painted Details by Borondo. Signed And Numbered. Spanish talent Borondo has produced a huge number of impressive walls this year and to top off the year, came to visit us a few weeks ago. He used his "Glass Scratching" technique to produce this stunning portrait of a girl named Despina. We've printed a faithful version of the artwork which has since had more details added by hand by the Spaniard himself. It's entitled "El Peso De La Corona" (The Weight Of The Crown) and - even if we say so ourselves - it's beautiful.

name: Faith47 "Mysterium Tremendum Et Fascinans"
description:
Faith47
"Mysterium Tremendum Et Fascinans"
Edition: 47
Size: 56 x 56 cm
Nine layer hand-pulled screen-print on on Fabriano Tiepolo 290gsm with four deckled edges.
Signed And Numbered.

Faith47 returns for her second print with us after her first was an instant sell-out. And she delivers it with the casual grace of a master craftswoman. The release date of "Mysterium Tremendum Et Fascinans" was decided to coincide with the New Moon on December 2nd, 2013 which will happen at 5:22:19 PM MST (Mountain Standard Time)

This artwork was inspired by the german theologian Rudolf Otto, referencing his analysis of the spiritual experience that, in his view, underlies all belief in deities, the supernatural, the sacred, the holy and transcendent. 
He calls this experience "numinous," and designated the Latin phrase: mysterium tremendum et fascinans.
The numinous is "wholly other"-- entirely different from anything we experience in ordinary life. 
It evokes a reaction of silence. But the numinous is also a mysterium tremendum which is the tendency to invoke fear and trembling with its overwhelming power. 
Finally, the numinous presents itself as fascinans, merciful and gracious with a tendency to attract, fascinate and compel. -- Faith47

"Mysterium Tremendum Et Fascinans" will be available in our store right here on Monday, December 2nd at 7PM UK for 119.99£ each.
Timezone conversions : (Melbourne: 6.00AM, New York: 2.00PM, Los Angeles: 11.00AM, Tokyo: 4.00AM, Moscow: 11.00PM)

name: 2501 "Hayagriva"
description:
2501
"Hayagriva"
Edition: 35
Size: 50 x 70 cm
One Layer Screen-print on Somerset paper.
Hand Finished With Spray Paint and Ink.
Signed And Numbered.

2501 returns for his second print with us after his first was a quick sell-out. He specialises in creating gigantic murals with his signature black and white wavy lines.

This release, entitled “Hayagriva” is a horse-headed avatar of the god Vishnu. In Hinduism, the story represents the triumph of pure knowledge, guided by the hand of God, over the demonic forces of passion and darkness. With this print, his skilled use of inks has created a hypnotic masterpiece that seems to come alive on the page. Simply beautiful. 

Available on Wednesday, November 13th at 4PM UK

name: Pixel Pancho "Rusted Mickey"
description: For the first time ever, StreetArtNews are producing a unique time-limited edition screen-printed t-shirt in collaboration with famed Italian Street Artist Pixel Pancho. Produced by hand at our lab in Italy, these T-shirts are one of a kind and are sporting one of Pixel Pancho's iconic images, "Rusted Mickey". "Rusted Mickey" will only be available for purchase for 24 Hours starting 4PM on Friday September 20th. After this point, no other orders will be taken, and there will be no further opportunity to buy - this is a one-time-only print run with no stock held! The final edition size will be announced after ordering has closed. Turin, Italy-born Pixel Pancho has an unmistakable style, he paints whimsical robots on the streets. Unlike many street artists he has a formal background in art studying at the Academy of Fine Arts in Valencia, where he obtained his degree. His style is influenced by past painters such as Joaquin Sorolla and Salvador Dali as well as more current artists like Ron English and Takashi Murakami. His love for graffiti has taken him all around the world where he's painted huge robot-filled murals in places like Paris, Amsterdam and Warsaw. A rising star in the street art scene, he's definitely one to watch. Men: Fruit Of The Loom Black 100% Cotton Women: Gildan Soft Black 100% Cotton Men Sizes Ladies Sizes
